positions.description:
Responsible for management of the International Operations Division (IOD).   IOD consists of over 30 senior law enforcement officers and support staff strategically located in twenty overseas locations, providing domestic field offices and HQ staff, with assistance on ICE mission-related matters.   Primary functions include:
ï· Develop and implement policies, procedures, and strategies;
ï· Oversee the international planning, directing, and controlling of removal operations and air transportation;
ï· Direct the planning, organizing, and coordinating of briefings and information exchange opportunities;
ï· Negotiate agreements, memorandums of understanding and/or cooperation with foreign governments and other partner agencies;
ï· Maintain a budget of over $10million. Develop and prepare annual operational cost projections and expenditure proposals; coordinate with management regarding budget allocations, funding requests, and position allocations;
ï· Prepare performance work plans, conduct periodic and annual performance evaluations, and recommend awards and bonuses. Develop and initiate hiring plans, and conduct hiring;
ï· Facilitate the removal of special interest cases; and regularly negotiating with foreign governments and entities in facilitating removals both commercially and via special air charters, providing logistical assistance, and on-the- ground support.
